<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="_TheLordTitlesAndRL.css" /></head><body>

<div class="c130_3"> 
<div id="v130.3.1"><span class="H1121 s">Now these were the sons</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H3205 s">, which were born</span><span class="H2275 s"> unto him in Hebron</span><span class="H1060 s">; the firstborn</span><span class="H550 s"> Amnon</span><span class="H293 s">, of Ahinoam</span><span class="H3159 s"> the Jezreelitess</span><span class="H8145 s">; the second</span><span class="H1840 s"> Daniel</span><span class="H26 s">, of Abigail</span><span class="H3762 s"> the Carmelitess</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Daniel: or, Chileab 2Sam.3.3.)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.2"><span class="H7992 s">The third</span><span class="H53 s">, Absalom</span><span class="H1121 s"> the son</span><span class="H4601 s"> of Maachah</span><span class="H1323 s"> the daughter</span><span class="H8526 s"> of Talmai</span><span class="H4428 s"> king</span><span class="H1650 s"> of Geshur</span><span class="H7243 s">: the fourth</span><span class="H138 s">, Adonijah</span><span class="H1121 s"> the son</span><span class="H2294 s"> of Haggith</span>:</div> 
<div id="v130.3.3"><span class="H2549 s">The fifth</span><span class="H8203 s">, Shephatiah</span><span class="H37 s"> of Abital</span><span class="H8345 s">: the sixth</span><span class="H3507 s">, Ithream</span><span class="H5698 s"> by Eglah</span><span class="H802 s"> his wife</span>.</div> 
<div id="v130.3.4"><span class="H8337 s"><i>These</i> six</span><span class="H3205 s"> were born</span><span class="H2275 s"> unto him in Hebron</span><span class="H4427 s">; and there he reigned</span><span class="H7651 s"> seven</span><span class="H8141 s"> years</span><span class="H8337 s"> and six</span><span class="H2320 s"> months</span><span class="H3389 s">: and in Jerusalem</span><span class="H4427 s"> he reigned</span><span class="H7970 s"> thirty</span><span class="H7969 s"> and three</span><span class="H8141 s"> years</span>.</div> 
<div id="v130.3.5"><span class="H3205 s">And these were born</span><span class="H3389 s"> unto him in Jerusalem</span><span class="H8092 s">; Shimea</span><span class="H7727 s">, and Shobab</span><span class="H5416 s">, and Nathan</span><span class="H8010 s">, and Solomon</span><span class="H702 s">, four</span><span class="H1340 s">, of Bathshua</span><span class="H1323 s"> the daughter</span><span class="H5988 s"> of Ammiel</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Shimea: or, Shammua 2.Sam.5.14.) (Bathshua: or, Bathsheba 2Sam.11.13.) (Ammiel: or, Eliam 2.Sam.11.3.)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.6"><span class="H2984 s">Ibhar</span><span class="H476 s"> also, and Elishama</span><span class="H467 s">, and Eliphelet</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Elishama: or, Elishua 2Sa.5.15.)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.7"><span class="H5052 s">And Nogah</span><span class="H5298 s">, and Nepheg</span><span class="H3309 s">, and Japhia</span>,</div> 
<div id="v130.3.8"><span class="H476 s">And Elishama</span><span class="H450 s">, and Eliada</span><span class="H467 s">, and Eliphelet</span><span class="H8672 s">, nine</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Eliada: or, Beeliada IChro.14.7.)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.9"><span class="H1121 s"><i>These were</i> all the sons</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H1121 s">, beside the sons</span><span class="H6370 s"> of the concubines</span><span class="H8559 s">, and Tamar</span><span class="H269 s"> their sister</span>.</div> 
<div id="v130.3.10"><span class="H8010 s">And Solomon's</span><span class="H1121 s"> son</span><span class="H7346 s"> <i>was</i> Rehoboam</span><span class="H29 s">, Abia</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H609 s">, Asa</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H3092 s">, Jehoshaphat</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Abia: or, Abijam I.king.15.1.)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.11"><span class="H3141 s">Joram</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H274 s">, Ahaziah</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H3101 s">, Joash</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Ahaziah: or, Azariah 2.Chr.22.6.& 21.17.)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.12"><span class="H558 s">Amaziah</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H5838 s">, Azariah</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H3147 s">, Jotham</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Azariah: or, Uzziah 2.king.15.30.)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.13"><span class="H271 s">Ahaz</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H2396 s">, Hezekiah</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H4519 s">, Manasseh</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span>,</div> 
<div id="v130.3.14"><span class="H526 s">Amon</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H2977 s">, Josiah</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span>.</div> 
<div id="v130.3.15"><span class="H1121 s">And the sons</span><span class="H2977 s"> of Josiah</span><span class="H1060 s"> <i>were</i>, the firstborn</span><span class="H3110 s"> Johanan</span><span class="H8145 s">, the second</span><span class="H3079 s"> Jehoiakim</span><span class="H7992 s">, the third</span><span class="H6667 s"> Zedekiah</span><span class="H7243 s">, the fourth</span><span class="H7967 s"> Shallum</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Johanan: or, Jehochaz 2.kin.23.30.) (Jehoiakim: or, Eliakim 2.kin.23.34.) (Zedekiah: or, Mathaniah.2.kin.24.17.)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.16"><span class="H1121 s">And the sons</span><span class="H3079 s"> of Jehoiakim</span><span class="H3204 s">: Jeconiah</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span><span class="H6667 s">, Zedekiah</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Jeconiah: also called, Jehoiachin 2kin.24.6, Zedekiah: or Coniah ier.22.24)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.17"><span class="H1121 s">And the sons</span><span class="H3204 s"> of Jeconiah</span><span class="H617 s">; Assir</span><span class="H7597 s">, Salathiel</span><span class="H1121 s"> his son</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Salathiel: Heb. Shealtiel)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.18"><span class="H4443 s">Malchiram</span><span class="H6305 s"> also, and Pedaiah</span><span class="H8137 s">, and Shenazar</span><span class="H3359 s">, Jecamiah</span><span class="H1953 s">, Hoshama</span><span class="H5072 s">, and Nedabiah</span>.</div> 
<div id="v130.3.19"><span class="H1121 s">And the sons</span><span class="H6305 s"> of Pedaiah</span><span class="H2216 s"> <i>were</i>, Zerubbabel</span><span class="H8096 s">, and Shimei</span><span class="H1121 s">: and the sons</span><span class="H2216 s"> of Zerubbabel</span><span class="H4918 s">; Meshullam</span><span class="H2608 s">, and Hananiah</span><span class="H8019 s">, and Shelomith</span><span class="H269 s"> their sister</span>:</div> 
<div id="v130.3.20"><span class="H2807 s">And Hashubah</span><span class="H169 s">, and Ohel</span><span class="H1296 s">, and Berechiah</span><span class="H2619 s">, and Hasadiah</span><span class="H3142 s">, Jushabhesed</span><span class="H2568 s">, five</span>.</div> 
<div id="v130.3.21"><span class="H1121 s">And the sons</span><span class="H2608 s"> of Hananiah</span><span class="H6410 s">; Pelatiah</span><span class="H3470 s">, and Jesaiah</span><span class="H1121 s">: the sons</span><span class="H7509 s"> of Rephaiah</span><span class="H1121 s">, the sons</span><span class="H770 s"> of Arnan</span><span class="H1121 s">, the sons</span><span class="H5662 s"> of Obadiah</span><span class="H1121 s">, the sons</span><span class="H7935 s"> of Shechaniah</span>.</div> 
<div id="v130.3.22"><span class="H1121 s">And the sons</span><span class="H7935 s"> of Shechaniah</span><span class="H8098 s">; Shemaiah</span><span class="H1121 s">: and the sons</span><span class="H8098 s"> of Shemaiah</span><span class="H2407 s">; Hattush</span><span class="H3008 s">, and Igeal</span><span class="H1282 s">, and Bariah</span><span class="H5294 s">, and Neariah</span><span class="H8202 s">, and Shaphat</span><span class="H8337 s">, six</span>.</div> 
<div id="v130.3.23"><span class="H1121 s">And the sons</span><span class="H5294 s"> of Neariah</span><span class="H454 s">; Elioenai</span><span class="H2396 s">, and Hezekiah</span><span class="H5840 s">, and Azrikam</span><span class="H7969 s">, three</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Hezekiah: Heb. Hiskijah)</span></div> 
<div id="v130.3.24"><span class="H1121 s">And the sons</span><span class="H454 s"> of Elioenai</span><span class="H1939 s"> <i>were</i>, Hodaiah</span><span class="H475 s">, and Eliashib</span><span class="H6411 s">, and Pelaiah</span><span class="H6126 s">, and Akkub</span><span class="H3110 s">, and Johanan</span><span class="H1806 s">, and Dalaiah</span><span class="H6054 s">, and Anani</span><span class="H7651 s">, seven</span>.</div></div>

